==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grabble
<hw>Grab"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Grabbled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Grabbling</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Freq.
of <ets>grab</ets>; cf. D. <ets>grabbelen</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To grope; to feel with the hands.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He puts his hands into his pockets, and keeps a
<qex>grabbling</qex> and fumbling.</q> <rj><qau>Selden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To lie prostrate on the belly; to sprawl on the
ground; to grovel.</def> <rj><au>Ainsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grace</ent>⟦br⟧
